video.title: Victorious
video.synopsis: When aspiring singer Tori Vega joins the eccentric students at Hollywood Arts High, she struggles to fit in with the amazingly talented teens.

episodes.synopsis: After Tori fills in for her ailing sister in a big musical showcase, she's asked to enroll at an elite performing arts high school.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Tori goes all out to master an iconic Hollywood Arts monologue in Sikowitz's class. Meanwhile, Andr√© and Robbie join a ballet class to meet girls.
episodes.title: The Bird Scene

episodes.synopsis: Tori has to defend herself after Jade claims Tori hurt her in a stage fighting exercise. Meanwhile, Trina has to fend off Robbie's advances.
episodes.title: Stage Fighting

episodes.synopsis: Tori accidentally gets Beck fired from a small role in a movie, then must figure out a way to get him his job back. Meanwhile, Robbie has nightmares.
episodes.title: Beck's Big Break

episodes.synopsis: Tori gets the lead in a school musical, but freaks out when a stage makeup project goes awry and she's left looking like a zombie on opening night.
episodes.title: Tori the Zombie

episodes.synopsis: After a jealous Jade dumps Beck, she soon regrets it and recruits Tori to help get him back. Meanwhile, Trina puts on a one-woman show.
episodes.title: Jade Dumps Beck

episodes.synopsis: Tori writes Trina a song as a present for her birthday. An ungrateful Trina turns the song into cash by selling it, enraging Tori.
episodes.title: The Birthweek Song

episodes.synopsis: Tori suggests Robbie capture videos of students' everyday lives to increase blog traffic, but when the camera is turned on Tori, she asks him to stop.
episodes.title: Robarazzi

episodes.synopsis: When a hot new filmmaker comes to Hollywood Arts, the kids are excited to work on his project. But the film is released and they aren't given credit.
episodes.title: A Film By Dale Squires

episodes.synopsis: As the kids prepare for a big play, Rex is accidentally sucked into a giant fan and Tori is responsible. It's up to Tori to save Rex's life.
episodes.title: Rex Dies

episodes.synopsis: Sikowitz recruits the gang to form a children's band for a friend's party. A leaked video of the group's performance embarrasses Andre.
episodes.title: The Diddly-Bops

episodes.synopsis: When Tori finds out that Cat's dating her ex, her jealousy threatens to ruin their relationship. Meanwhile, Trina uses fish for a strange reason.
episodes.title: Cat's New Boyfriend

episodes.synopsis: Sikowitz invites the gang to have a sleepover at his house in order to teach them a lesson in method acting.
episodes.title: Sleepover at Sikowitz's

episodes.synopsis: The kids are excited to hear that they'll be the stars of a reality show at Hollywood Arts. Meanwhile, Trina and Robbie must work at The Grub Truck.
episodes.title: The Wood

episodes.synopsis: Tori discovers that her friends have been secretly going to a fancy restaurant instead of playing in an annual ping pong tournament.
episodes.title: The Great Ping-Pong Scam

episodes.synopsis: Tori agrees to help Jade find a theater to perform a play Jade wrote, but the sponsor demands changes that will ruin Jade's play.
episodes.title: Wok Star

episodes.synopsis: A heat wave hits L.A. and the gang heads for the beach in Beck's RV. But once there, they get trapped inside the RV as the temperature rises.
episodes.title: Survival of the Hottest

episodes.synopsis: A delayed flight leaves Tori no time to finish a project with her friends. She attempts to work with them over video chat, but complications arise.
episodes.title: Wi-Fi in the Sky

episodes.synopsis: Cat and Jade enter a karaoke contest at a club but they find out the contest was rigged. Robbie tries to impress some girls from a normal high school.
episodes.title: Freak the Freak Out: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: After losing the karaoke contest to the club owner's daughters, Cat and Jade seek help from Tori to win the contest.
episodes.title: Freak the Freak Out: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The Full Moon Jam is coming up. The cutest boy in school wants to perform a duet with Tori, but she finds out he has a reputation.
episodes.title: Beggin' on Your Knees

episodes.synopsis: Tori auditions for a role in a movie. But after exaggerating on her resume, she gets hired as a stunt double who has to fall off a building.
episodes.title: Beck Falls for Tori

episodes.synopsis: Tori has to be Trina's assistant for a month. But the only way Trina will call off the bet is if Tori wins a private Ke$ha concert.
episodes.title: Ice Cream for Ke$ha

episodes.synopsis: Tori is excited when she gets cast as the lead in the school play, but she has to deal with her very unhappy understudy, Jade.
episodes.title: Tori Gets Stuck

episodes.synopsis: Tori rallies the gang into having prom at Hollywood Arts, but the event ruins Jade's art project -- and now she's out for revenge.
episodes.title: Prom Wrecker

episodes.synopsis: Spring Break looks bleak until Tori gets everyone a free vacation. But the destination is a tourist nightmare where things go from bad to worse.
episodes.title: Locked Up!: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: When the kids try to free Tori from prison and end up imprisoning themselves, the Chancellor grants Tori and her friends one prison performance.
episodes.title: Locked Up!: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: When Principal Eikner leaves Hollywood Arts, the school hires a new principal who makes all the students re-audition in order to keep their spots.
episodes.title: Helen Back Again

episodes.synopsis: Trina stars in Tori's directorial debut, and there's a big accident on opening night. Lane wants to find out what went wrong.
episodes.title: Who Did It to Trina?

episodes.synopsis: The kids take Sikowitz to the theater to celebrate his 10-year teaching anniversary, but the play's subject matter sends Sikowitz into a depression.
episodes.title: Tori Tortures Teacher

episodes.synopsis: Andr√© spends time with Jade, working on a song, and develops a crush on her. Tori tries to help him get over his crush, but nothing seems to work.
episodes.title: Jade Gets Crushed

episodes.synopsis: The kids have to build a float fast. But when the float breaks down in a bad neighborhood, can the kids recover and save their chance to be on TV?
episodes.title: Terror on Cupcake Street

episodes.synopsis: Christopher Cane, the actor who plays Rex, is our host for an in-depth look into the stars of Victorious, and their hilarious bloopers/outtakes.
episodes.title: Blooptorious
